Package infodynamics.measures.continuous.gaussian

Class Summary
ConditionalMutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateGaussian Computes the differential conditional mutual information of two given multivariate sets of observations, assuming that the probability distribution function for these observations is a multivariate Gaussian distribution.
EntropyCalculatorGaussian Computes the differential entropy of a given set of observations, assuming that the probability distribution function for these observations is Gaussian.
EntropyCalculatorMultiVariateGaussian Computes the differential entropy of a given multivariate set of observations, assuming that the probability distribution function for these observations is a multivariate Gaussian distribution.
MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateGaussian Computes the differential mutual information of two given multivariate sets of observations, assuming that the probability distribution function for these observations is a multivariate Gaussian distribution.
MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateWithDiscreteGaussian Computes the differential mutual information between a given multivariate set of observations (assuming that the probability distribution function for these observations is a multivariate Gaussian distribution) and a discrete variable.
